Abstract = {{The structural, electronic, magnetic properties of Mn3XC (X = Al, Zn and
   Ga) antiperovskites have been investigated using first principles
   calculations based on Full-Potential Linearized Augmented Plane-Wave
   (FP-LAPW) method. Generalized Gradient Approximation with
   parameterization by Perdew (GGA-PBESol) is used to take into account the
   electron exchange-correlation interaction. Structural optimization is
   performed by fitting calculated data (energy-volume) to Birch-Murnaghan
   equation of state. Lattice constants increase in the order Mn3AlC ->
   Mn3GaC -> Mn3ZnC. Electronic results show that there is no bandgap near
   the Fermi level. While the magnetism in these compounds is derived
   mainly from Mn atom. Finally, thermodynamic properties, including bulk
   modulus, heat capacities, thermal expansion and Gruneisen parameter, are
   computed using quasi-harmonic Debye model and analyzed in detail.}},
